Top 10 Medical Colleges in Maharashtra for 2020 MBBS Admission

Maharashtra is well-known for the highest standards of academic excellence coupled with state-of-art infrastructure. It comprises of the top medical colleges in Maharashtra that provide high-quality education. These colleges provide an extensive range of academic programs in MBBS, BDS, BAMS, BHMS, B.Pharmacy, MD, MS, M.Pharmacy along with certificate and diploma courses of study.

Every year, most of the students take admission in medical colleges in Maharashtra for pursuing MBBS. But the admission to these medical colleges in Maharashtra is on the basis of NEET-UG. In this article, we provide the complete detail of the top 10 medical colleges in Maharashtra for MBBS admission such as college ranking, seat availability, admission procedure, fees structure:

  • Shri Vasantrao Naik Govt. Medical Hospital
  • Topiwala National Medical College

Shri Vasantrao Naik Govt. Medical Hospita

Shri Vasantrao Naik Govt. Medical Hospital is one of the top medical colleges in Maharashtra which was established in 1989. It is accredited from the Medical Council of India (MCI) and it is affiliated to Maharashtra University of Health Sciences. It provides 11 courses across three streams such as Medical, Paramedical, Science, and across 4 degrees such as MBBS, MD, MS (Surgery), Diploma. This college is functional and managed by the Government of Maharashtra and provides all the basic facilities to the aspiring medical students.

Location

Shri Vasantrao Naik Govt. Medical Hospital is located at Waghapur Road, Palswadi Camp, Civil Lines, Yavatmal, Maharashtra, India

Topiwala National Medical College

Topiwala National Medical College is one of the leading medical institutes which was established in 1964. It provides a wide range of training courses in several medical courses and allied branches including 9 super-specialty courses. The students can take admission to this college on the basis of the NEET Exam. It has more than 250 senior faculty members who are supported by 400 resident doctors. It comprises 5 lecture halls with a seating capacity of 130 students each, well-equipped laboratories, department libraries, research lab, museum, and seminar room.

Location

Topiwala National Medical College is located at Dr. A. L. Nair Road, Mumbai, Maharashtra, India

It provides 34 courses across two streams such as Medical, Paramedical, and 5 degrees such as MBBS, BPMT, MD, MS (Surgery), Diploma.

Grant Medical College

Grant Medical College is one of the oldest and premier educational institutions in Mumbai, Maharashtra which was established in 1845. It is affiliated to the Maharashtra University of Health Sciences located in Nashik.

Every year, approx 250 students take admission in the undergraduate course and 100 students to the postgraduate course. All these medical courses are recognized by MCI. The MBBS course offered by the Grant Medical College is a four and a half year period followed by a one year compulsory rotating residential internship. It has Clinical Departments, Pre-clinical Departments, and Para-clinical Departments.

Location

Grant Medical College is located at J J Marg, Nagpada-Mumbai Central, Off Jijabhoy Road, Mumbai, Maharashtra, India

Byramjee Jeejeebhoy Government Medical College

Byramjee Jeejeebhoy Government Medical College is one of the top medical colleges in Maharashtra which was established in 1946. It was affiliated to the University of Pune in 1949 but now affiliated to the Maharashtra University of Health Sciences, Nashik, Maharashtra. It also has a hospital inside the same campus known as Sassoon General Hospital. It provides courses on several disciplines such as M.B.B.S, M.Ch, M.D, M.S, and more. Byramjee Jeejeebhoy Government Medical College provides admission to students on the basis of their NEET scores.

Location

Byramjee Jeejeebhoy Government Medical College is located at Pune, Maharashtra. Pune International Airport is 8.4 km away and students can reach the campus in about 28 mins. Pune Railway Station is 1 km away from the institute. Pune Main Bus Stand is 10 km away from this college.

Bharati Vidyapeeth medical college (Deemed to be University)

Bharati Vidyapeeth (Deemed to be University) is one of the top medical colleges in Pune, Maharashtra which was established in 1964. It recognized by the Government of India. All the courses provided by this are approved by UGC and respective statutory councils. It is a Member of the Association of Indian Universities (AIU) and Association of Commonwealth Universities (ACU). It comprises two campuses in Pune such as Dhankawadi and Erandwane. It includes more than 1600 Teachers, 12 faculties, more than 250 Programmes, and 29 Constituent Institutions including 3 Research Institutes. It also organizes a summer internship program.

Location

Bharati Vidyapeeth medical college is located at LBS Road next to Alka Talkies 13, Sadashiv Peth, Pune, Maharashtra. Deccan Gymkhana Bus Station is 1 km away and Pune Railway Station is 4.7 km away and Pune International Airport is 12.2 km away from the Bharati Vidyapeeth.

Armed Forces Medical College

Armed Forces Medical College is one of the premier medical institutions in Pune, Maharashtra which was established in 1948 through the merger of several defense medical units. It holds the status of a center of excellence for education and research. It is administered by the countrys armed forces. It provides postgraduate, undergraduate, and postgraduate diploma programs in fields of nursing, pharmacy, medicine, dentistry, and paramedics. The degree offered by Armed Forces Medical College is approved by the MCI (Medical Council of India) and has affiliation of Maharashtra University of Health Sciences.

Smt. Kashibai Navale Medical College and General hospital

Smt. Kashibai Navale Medical College and General hospital is one of the top medical colleges in Pune, Maharashtra which was started in 2007. It is affiliated with Maharashtra University of Health Sciences, Nasik, and has sanction from the MCI (Medical Council of India). The degree provided by Smt. Kashibai Navale Medical College and General hospital is recognized by the Medical Council of India and also by the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare. It provides various Postgraduate courses in the subjects of Biochemistry, Pharmacology, Pathology, Microbiology, Community Medicine.

Maharashtra Institute of Medical Sciences & Research

Maharashtra Institute of Medical Sciences & Research is one of the top medical colleges in Latur, Maharashtra which was established in 1989. It is managed and run by Maharashtra Academy of Engineering and Educational Research, Pune. It is affiliated to Maharashtra University of Health Sciences, Nashik, and approved by the MCI (Medical Council of India). It provides a medical course at the undergraduate level such as Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS). Every year, 100 students take admission to this UG program. It offers several modern medical facilities to its students.

KJ Somaiya Medical College & Research Center

KJ Somaiya Medical College is the old private medical college which was established in 1991. It is affiliated to the state-run Maharashtra University of Health Sciences and approved by the MCI (Medical Council of India). It provides undergraduate as well as postgraduate courses. It has a 22.5-acre campus with all the required amenities such as High-tech lecture theatres, medical laboratories, and an auditorium. The campus has its own hospital by the name of KJ Somaiya Hospital.
